# Wiki-Beta Runtime and Data Flow

```mermaid
flowchart LR
  subgraph RT["Runtime Boundary"]
    direction TB
    subgraph NX["Next.js Runtime"]
      APP["app/(shell)/wiki-beta/page.tsx"]
      MOD["modules/wiki-beta<br/>interfaces/components + queries"]
      APP --> MOD
    end

    subgraph FN["Firebase Functions Runtime"]
      PY["py_fn<br/>Callable handlers"]
      RAG["rag_query"]
      REIDX["rag_reindex_document"]
      PY --> RAG
      PY --> REIDX
    end

    MOD -->|"httpsCallable: rag_query(account_id, query, top_k)"| PY
    MOD -->|"httpsCallable: rag_reindex_document(account_id, doc_id, json_gcs_uri, ...)"| PY
    RAG -->|"retrieve + answer"| OUT1["RAG answer + citations"]
    REIDX -->|"re-ingest from json_gcs_uri"| OUT2["RAG status refresh"]
    OUT1 --> MOD
    OUT2 --> MOD
  end

  subgraph DM["Account Data Model (Firestore)"]
    direction TB
    A["accounts/{accountId}"]
    M["members/{userId}"]
    T["teams/{teamId}"]
    S["spaces/{spaceId}"]
    F["files/{fileId}"]
    D["documents/{documentId}"]
    P["pages/{pageId}"]
    C["chunks/{chunkId}"]
    V["vectors/{vectorId}"]
    Q["rag_queries/{queryId}"]
    ANS["rag_answers/{answerId}"]

    A --> M
    A --> T
    A --> S
    A --> F
    A --> D
    A --> P
    A --> C
    A --> V
    A --> Q
    A --> ANS

    F --> D
    D --> C
    C --> V
    S --> P
    S --> D
    D -. "Document to Page (manual curation)" .-> P
  end

  subgraph PIPE["RAG Ingestion + Query Pipeline"]
    direction TB
    U["Upload File"] --> ST["Storage (file)"]
    ST --> FR["Create File Record"]
    FR --> PF["Parse File"]
    PF --> CD["Create Document"]
    CD --> CH["Chunk Document"]
    CH --> CC["Create Chunks"]
    CC --> EM["Embedding"]
    EM --> CV["Create Vectors"]
    CV --> RS["RAG Search"]
    RS --> RA["Answer"]
  end

  FR --> F
  CD --> D
  CC --> C
  CV --> V
  RS --> Q
  RA --> ANS
  Q --> RAG
  V --> RAG
```

## Migration Phases

- Phase 1: callable payload requires `account_id`.
- Phase 2: storage-trigger ingestion requires account binding (`metadata.account_id` or `uploads/{accountId}/...`).
- Phase 3 (current): Firestore reads/writes and RAG retrieval are account-scoped only.

## Field Summary

- accounts/{accountId}
  - name
  - type (personal | organization)
  - ownerId
- accounts/{accountId}/spaces/{spaceId}
  - name
  - description
  - visibility
- accounts/{accountId}/files/{fileId}
  - filename
  - storagePath
  - mimeType
  - size
  - uploadedBy
  - status (uploaded | parsed | chunked | embedded)
  - createdAt
- accounts/{accountId}/documents/{documentId}
  - fileId
  - title
  - text
  - metadata
  - spaceId
  - createdAt
- accounts/{accountId}/chunks/{chunkId}
  - documentId
  - text
  - order
  - tokenCount
- accounts/{accountId}/vectors/{vectorId}
  - chunkId
  - embedding
  - indexId
- accounts/{accountId}/pages/{pageId}
  - title
  - content
  - spaceId
  - linkedDocuments[]
- accounts/{accountId}/rag_queries/{queryId}
  - query
  - userId
  - createdAt

## Notes

- app/(shell)/wiki-beta is the route orchestrator.
- modules/wiki-beta owns UI composition and query adapters.
- py_fn owns callable execution for RAG query and document reindex.
- wiki-beta and wiki must remain isolated by lint import boundaries.
